The paper deals with the capacity of time-and frequency-selective multipath fading channels in the ultrawide-band (UWB) regime when training signals are used for channel estimation at the receiver. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a model for sparse multipath channels, which involves the use of short-time Fourier (STF) basis functions, and studies the impact of multipath sparsity on spectral efficiency. This suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of its results for channel learning and capacity attainment, which may also relate to communication and networking (cs.COM).
